 Lynn , from Chippenham , had to stop taking medication that enables her to move without pain as she suffers from a painful condition callled hip displasia .
Lynn and husband Liam tried for a baby for three years so stopped taking pain relief for her scoliosis and hip dysplasia symptoms .
The condition means the ball and socket joint of her hip has not formed properly , which causes pain .
Lynn has to stop to taking the drugs for the baby .